{
  "$comment": [
    "Curated icon set for semantic-ui, sourced from Lucide (ISC-licensed).",
    "Each key is a STABLE SEMANTIC TOKEN referenced from UiNodes (icon: \"delete\").",
    "The value is the concrete Lucide icon id used to build the sprite.",
    "",
    "This indirection is what makes the icon library swappable: to move to a",
    "different library, re-point these values at that library's ids and",
    "regenerate — app JSON that uses the semantic tokens never changes.",
    "",
    "Raw Lucide names not listed here still work at runtime IF present in the",
    "sprite; the 'passthrough' block below pulls in extra raw ids verbatim so",
    "authors can reference e.g. 'star' directly without inventing an alias.",
    "",
    "Regenerate the sprite after editing:  npm run build:icons"
  ],

  "aliases": {
    "add":          "plus",
    "edit":         "pencil",
    "delete":       "trash-2",
    "remove":       "minus",
    "save":         "save",
    "copy":         "copy",
    "close":        "x",
    "check":        "check",
    "confirm":      "check",
    "cancel":       "x",
    "send":         "send",
    "reset":        "rotate-ccw",
    "refresh":      "refresh-cw",

    "back":         "arrow-left",
    "forward":      "arrow-right",
    "up":           "arrow-up",
    "down":         "arrow-down",
    "home":         "house",
    "menu":         "menu",
    "more":         "ellipsis",
    "more-vertical":"ellipsis-vertical",
